parameters:
In a sudden turn of events, the two hurriedly prepared
themselves and, following the instructions of the debt
collector, set sail for the designated island.

\N<Sailor>Oh, there it is! That's the deserted island where you'll be
staying.
MAP_World_1
\N<Luna>Wow... such a naturally rich and beautiful island...♪

\N<Sailor>It's a remote island in the middle of nowhere, but it's
swarming with adventurers all aiming for a quick fortune.
\N<Taro>("This is so depressing"... I can't say that...)

\N<Sailor>Don't worry, there are inns and places to eat and drink.
It's an island where you won't have trouble living, and
there's even a bit of entertainment.♪

\N<Sailor>However... I've heard rumors that couples who come to this
island end up falling out and breaking up... but, nah, it's
nothing to worry about.
\N<Luna>...Hm??

\N<Sailor>My bad, my bad♪ Let's start over—this is your first time
landing on the island, right? I'll give you a brief rundown
of what's here.
\N<Sailor>First off, let's start with the island's symbolic structure.
MAP_Tower

\N<Sailor>Towering in the back of the island is the \C[27]Tower
Dungeon\C[2]! Adventurers gather here with the goal of
conquering it.

\N<Sailor>I've heard that the bounty for the boss on the top floor is
outrageous—what kind of fearsome monster it could be... even
a sailor like me can't imagine, next...
MAP_Village

\N<Sailor>The \C[27]village\C[2], which serves as a base for
adventurers, is fairly bustling—there's a weapon shop, an
item shop, a guild, and even an open-air bath. Impressive,
right?

\N<Sailor>Well, if you're going to the dungeon, you should definitely
prepare thoroughly in this village first. You should at
least be able to get the bare essentials ready.
MAP_Colosseum

\N<Sailor>There's also an easier way to make money than going to the
dungeon—the den of the brave, the \C[27]Colosseum\C[2].

\N<Sailor>If you're confident in your skills, you should give it a
try. Defeat strong opponents and get a big payday!
MAP_Slum

\N<Sailor>This island also has a \C[27]slum\C[2]—second only to the
dungeon in terms of poor security. Brothels, dance bars,
massage parlors... it's a lawless zone where anything goes.

\N<Sailor>A young lady like you shouldn't get too close—unless you
want to make money the easy way! Gah-hah-hah-hah!
MAP_Wood

\N<Sailor>That huge tree is called the \C[27]World Tree\C[2]... but to
be honest, I'm not really sure why it exists or why it's
called that.

\N<Sailor>Rumor has it that if [Color_27]only women\C[2] go there,
they can hear something. I've been there myself but didn't
hear anything, so it must be true.
MAP_Beach

\N<Sailor>And lastly, there's the \C[27]beach\C[2]! It's just a sandy
shore, but this beach is known for having lots of
\C[3]crabs\C[2].

\N<Sailor>They're not particularly valuable, but you can make enough
to get some initial equipment.

\N<Sailor>I'll let you in on a good tip—the \C[3]big crabs\C[2] that
occasionally appear at the back of the beach can earn you a
bit more.

\N<Sailor>When you go to the beach, it might be worth looking for
them.

\N<Sailor>...That's about it for an overview. If you want to know more
details, you should go check them out for yourself.

\N<Luna>Thank you for the explanation. Now I understand what's on
the island.♪

\N<Sailor>Hehehe♪ No problem at all. We're about to arrive—get ready
to disembark!
